reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Say Goodbye to Bed Shakes: Krisler Adjustable Threaded Bed Frame Anti-Shake Tool
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the Krisler Adjustable Threaded Bed Frame Anti-Shake Tool, and it has completely transformed my sleeping experience. If you've ever been bothered by the annoying bed shakes caused by a loose bed frame or headboard, this simple yet ingenious tool is the solution you've been searching for.Installation was a breeze – it took me just a few minutes to attach the adjustable threaded rods to my bed frame and headboard. The best part? The design is incredibly versatile, making it compatible with various bed sizes and styles. No need for complicated tools or professional help; it's a DIY fix that anyone can handle.The difference it made is remarkable. Once installed, the bed frame became rock-solid, eliminating any wobbles or shakes. Now, I can enjoy a peaceful night's sleep without being disturbed by every movement. The headboard stoppers work like a charm, preventing any loosening and ensuring that my bed stays stable and secure.I appreciate the durability and sturdiness of this anti-shake tool. The materials used are of high quality, promising long-term reliability. Despite its robust build, it remains discreet and doesn't interfere with the overall aesthetics of my bed.What sets the Krisler Anti-Shake Tool apart is its effectiveness in preventing not only bed shakes but also noise. No more creaks or squeaks when getting in or out of bed – it's a silent solution to a common problem.In addition to its functionality, I appreciate the thoughtful design that allows for easy adjustments if needed. The threaded rods can be fine-tuned to fit snugly, ensuring a personalized and secure fit for every user.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more squeaky wood joints
reviews.reviewText: Husband made our headboard, rails, posts, and footboard, but the posts are supposedly not wide enough and that’s why the headboard squeaks every time we roll over in our sleep or get up at night for water or the toilet. I had a long bed pillow stuffed between the wall and headboard but it was getting dusty. These things work great and aren’t visible, so there’s nothing to look out of place. They’re very easy to install. He did so in under 5 minutes I think.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2022
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE: I removed it from my wall and it took off several layers of paint and a bit of drywall. If you’re renting and aren’t supposed to have nails, etc in your walls, I recommend putting a different adhesive on the back such as removable mounting tape. That’s not my situation, but in case it’s yours, now you know.Our dogs jump up and play on our bed sometimes and we were annoyed with our headboard shaking up against the wall. We live in on base housing so we didn’t want to risk damage to our walls either. These have definitely stopped most of the shaking! Vigorous movement can sometimes make the headboard lightly “slam” into them, but it really isn’t that noisy or anything!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Didn't quite fit my headboard on length, not the fault of anyone but me. There is a board across the top of mine that adds nearly an inch to the distance from the wall. The sticky part is too wide to fit the side of that board. If I put it below the board it doesn't reach the wall. The sticky works great though, it's still on there after several weeks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just buy them
reviews.reviewText: I bought these due to having a high headboard and hated how it hit the wall all the time. These have been well worth the purchase and if anything happens to them, I will buy them again. My only fault with these is the sticky part is supposed to go on the wall. I have seen where some people but the sticky to the headboard instead and wish I had done that for if we ever decide to re-arrange the furniture in the room. Due to how well it works, I'm afraid it will take the paint off the wall when/if they get removed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does the job.
reviews.reviewText: My bedframe is a couple inches away from the wall, like most are. BUT whenever the hubbs and I try to "wrestle" the bedframe hits the wall, making too much noise. I don't know about you but I'm not trying to wake my kids up so they can walk in on us trying to find out what the banging noise is. That is why we bought these. They were a little tricky to install at first because I was having a blonde moment and tried to put them in one at a time so the first one kept falling when trying to install the second. Only took me two tries before the light bulb went off and I decided to try placing them at the same time. This worked perfectly. They've stayed in placed after many "wrestling matches" so I recommend them.
Son muy útiles para evitar que los muebles dañen las paredes y evita el ruido de las cabeceras

Los utilice para la cabecera de mi cama, es de madera y muy grande, además de que es algo inestable, al más mínimo movimiento de la cama está hacia un golpeteo infernal. Opte por taladrarlas, y realmente solucionaron mi ruidoso problema. En mi caso el único inconveniente que encontré pese a enroscarlas hasta el maximo (ya que tiene un tornillo para elegir la separación del mueble a la pared) el espacio que dejó es bastante y he perdido algo de espacio funcional en mi habitación.

Ya hacía meses que quería comprarlos, es desesperante el escuchar como la cabecera de la cama pega, por qué no se alinea bien a la pared por el soclo que tiene la habitación. Ahora el materia es bueno, viene con sus adhesivos y una protección para las gomas que irán a la pared, debo decir que llegó más rápido de lo esperado y por el precio es una muy buena compra.
Ayuda si no puedes colocar directamente la cabecera a la pared. Gran artículo.
